<div class="content"><div class="main large">
    <h3>Modals</h3>
    Modals have a header (<i>.modal-header</i>), body (<i>.modal-body</i>), and footer (<i>.modal-footer</i>), all of which are wrapped in the <i>modal-content</i> class. The element used to trigger the modal uses <i>data-toggle="modal"</i> and <i>data-target</i> to launch the associated modal. The <i>modal-dialog</i> class is used to position the modal on the screen.
    <br><br>
    Modals that are smaller than the browser viewport will be centered in the middle of the screen. Modals that are larger, will take up the screen and scroll.
    <br><br>
    Include the class <i>fade</i> to fade the backdrop in and out when showing the modal.
    <br><br>

<code><pre>
&lt;button data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">
  Launch demo modal
&lt;/button>

&lt;div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1">
  &lt;div class="modal-dialog">
    &lt;div class="modal-content">
      &lt;div class="modal-header">
        &lt;button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&lt;i class="fa fa-times">&lt;/i>&lt;/button>
        &lt;h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Modal title&lt;/h4>
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div class="modal-body">
        This is the body of the modal.
      &lt;/div>
      &lt;div class="modal-footer">
        &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close&lt;/button>
        &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Save changes&lt;/button>
      &lt;/div>
    &lt;/div>
  &lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
</pre></code>
</div></div>

